    "what_description": "Cousinia aspera is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae. It is an annual herb with a height of 10-30 cm, and a spread of 5-10 cm, having leaves that are lance-shaped and serrated. The plant produces yellow flowers in a capitulum, with 10-20 florets, and is dioecious, meaning the male and female flowers are found on separate plants. The plant is native to the Mediterranean region and Western Asia, and is found in dry, stony areas and mountainous regions. Cousinia aspera is a species of high mountainous regions, and is often found in areas above 1,500 meters in elevation.",
